53.7	Liberal_democracy	Liberal democracy	Liberal democracy, also known as constitutional democracy, is a common form of representative democracy. According to the principles of liberal democracy, elections should be free and fair, and the political process should be competitive. Political pluralism is usually defined as the presence of multiple and distinct political parties.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/35/Parliament_building_Finland.jpg/175px-Parliament_building_Finland.jpg
